cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on logical (inter-)definability of linear equation systems. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of solvability problems for linear equation systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are possible categories as the paper involves studying the structure theory of finite rings and reductions among various solvability problems. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions closure properties for classes of queries, which could be related to game theory.
